Name.SpaSpp: Spina nasalis anterior - Spina nasalis posterior
Name.VPOcPHPOcP: Front point of the occlusal plane - Posterior point of the occlusal plane

Name.HPOcP: Posterior point of the occlusal plane
Name.VPOcP: Front point of the occlusal plane

TrainingText.A: Most dorsally located point of the anterior contour of the maxillary alveolar process in the mid-sagittal plane
TrainingText.ApOK1: Root tip of the upper central incisor
TrainingText.ApUK1: Root tip of the lower central incisor
TrainingText.Ar: Orientation point for the description of the ascending mandibular ramus; radiographic intersection between the (averaged) dorsal contour of the Ramus ascendens and the inferior border of the skull base; Not an anatomical point (Bj√∂rk, 1947)
TrainingText.B: Most dorsal point of the anterior contour of the mandibular alveolar process in the median-sagittal plane; according to Riolo et al. (1974), the B-Point is located in the area of the apical root third of the mandibular incisors
TrainingText.Calibration1: First reference point that is set on the ruler at 0cm
TrainingText.Calibration2: First reference point that is set on the ruler at 1cm
TrainingText.Go: (Go will be set automatically when Ar, Me, Tga, Tgp are placed) Jaw angle point; intersection of tangents to horizontal and ascending mandibular ramus
TrainingText.Goa: Intersection of the bisector of the jaw angle with the anatomical contour of the jaw angle
TrainingText.HPOcP: Most distal point of contact of the first molars (modified after Rakosi, 1988)
TrainingText.InOK1: Incisal edge of the upper central incisor
TrainingText.InUK1: Incisal edge of the lower central incisor
TrainingText.Li: Most anterior point of the lower lip
TrainingText.Ls: Most anterior point of the upper lip
TrainingText.Me: Furthest caudal point on the contour of the symphysis; deepest point of the bony chin
TrainingText.N: Anterior end of the sutura fronto-nasalis at the junction from the Osnasale to the Os frontale (mid-sagittal plane)
TrainingText.Pog: Most anterior point of mandibular symphysis in mid-sagittal plane; bony tip of chin
TrainingText.Pog2: Most protruding point of the chin
TrainingText.ProN: Most protruding point of the nose tip
TrainingText.S: Geometric center of the Sella turcica; constructed point in the mid-sagittal plane
TrainingText.Sp: (Sp will be set automatically when Me, N, Spa, Spp are placed) Intersection of the line N-Me with the spinaplanum
TrainingText.Spa: Most anteriorly located tip of the bony spinanasalis anterior in the mid-sagittal plane
TrainingText.Spp: The most posterior point of the nasal floor or bony palate; located at the extension of the anterior wall of the fossa pterygopalatina
TrainingText.Tga: Most caudally located point in the mandibular angle region; tangent point ( starting from Menton) to the inferior border of the horizontal mandibular ramus
TrainingText.Tgp: Most dorsally located point in the mandibular angle region; tangent point (starting from Articulare) to the posterior margin of the ascending mandibular ramus
TrainingText.VPOcP: (fPOcP will be set automatically when InUJ1, InLJ1 are placed) Halving the distance of incisor overbite in the final bite (Rakosi, 1988)
